      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p>Hello {first_name, \"there\"},</p><p>It's July. How did it end up being July? March and April seemed to last forever, but the last two months have passed in the blink of an eye. It's as if someone is messing around with time.</p><p>And talking of time…</p>"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The pandemic shows the need to embrace explainer journalism",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "koenig-heading",
        "tag": "h2",
        "version": 1,
        "renderVersion": "3.0"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Once you start paying attention to SEO, you realise how important it is to update your content online. And then, if you're smart, a little light goes off in your head, and you realise how very different digital content is from its printed equivalent. One of the great boons of the digital format is the ability to update things without having to entirely rewrite them - to see your website as a living document, not a moment in time caught in paper aspic. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Now, let's turn that idea around the other way: what's the price of ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 1,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "not",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " updating things?",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "In a pandemic, the answer is, of course, intentionally or not, you end up communicating poor, outdated information. ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "And then, as these tweets highlight, you have a problem: ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "embed",
        "url": "https://twitter.com/gerrymcgovern/status/1277569479128596480?s=21",
        "html": "<blockquote class=\"twitter-tweet\" data-width=\"550\"><p lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\">It does seem like most orgs have poor or non-existent processes and resources to review, update and where necessary remove published content in. That&#39;s particularly dangerous in a fast moving pandemic, where accurate information one week is misleading the next.</p>&mdash; Gerry McGovern - Black Lives Matter (@gerrymcgovern) <a href=\"https://twitter.com/gerrymcgovern/status/1277569479128596480?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw\">June 29, 2020</a></blockquote>\n<script async src=\"https://platform.twitter.com/widgets.js\" charset=\"utf-8\"></script>\n",
        "metadata": {
          "url": "https://twitter.com/gerrymcgovern/status/1277569479128596480",
          "author_name": "Gerry McGovern - Black Lives Matter",
          "author_url": "https://twitter.com/gerrymcgovern",
          "width": 550,
          "height": null,
          "cache_age": "3153600000",
          "provider_name": "Twitter",
          "provider_url": "http://www.twitter.com/",
          "version": "1.0"
        },
        "embedType": "rich"
      },
      {
        "type": "email",
        "html": "<p><em>You might need to click through to see it all.</em></p>"
