      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Six years ago, I wrote a piece on ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "explainer journalism",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://www.journalism.co.uk/news-commentary/-we-haven-t-even-scratched-surface-of-explainer-journalism-/s6/a556585/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " for journalism.co.uk. We have not moved on those ideas nearly quickly enough as an industry yet. We still remain deeply attached to the idea of a rolling series of updated news stories, rather than single, updated resources. The two are not mutually exclusive, of course. The single explainer can link to the news story, and the news story back to the explainer. But are you leaving stories up on your site with outdated Covid-19 info in them? If so, are you modifying them in some way to allow people to find the more updated information? ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "If not, you ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "are",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " unintentionally contributing to misinformation. People just don't pay attention to dates when they share things. They don't. That's why ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "The Guardian",
